This position was excel- lently chosen to watch the movements of Hannibal whose easiest road to Rome lay through Umbria by the Via Flaminia, which had been made a few years before by C. Flaminius. If com- municatione were kept up between the two consuls at Arretium and Ariminum they might hope to combine the forces when the route of the invaders was discovered. Precisely the same ar- rangements had been made to cover Rome in the Gallie war of 225 nc.
